WEBVTT

00:02.711 --> 00:05.630
<i>[rock music]</i>

00:05.714 --> 00:06.881
<i>kids:</i>
<i>Pig!</i>

00:06.965 --> 00:10.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:10.176 --> 00:10.552
<i>Goat!</i>

00:10.635 --> 00:13.471
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:13.555 --> 00:14.806
<i>Banana!</i>

00:14.889 --> 00:19.477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:19.561 --> 00:20.770
<i>Cricket!</i>

00:20.854 --> 00:28.153
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:33.533 --> 00:35.160
- A-a-a-achoo!

00:35.243 --> 00:38.413
<i>all:</i>
<i>Pig! Goat! Banana! Cricket!</i>

00:42.000 --> 00:44.961
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:45.044 --> 00:52.886
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:52.969 --> 00:54.304
- [gasps]

00:54.387 --> 00:56.473
"Popular Pickles" magazine
just came out with their

00:56.556 --> 00:58.767
Pickle of the Year
and it's my hero!

00:58.850 --> 00:59.976
P. Pickles Pickleman!

01:00.059 --> 01:01.811
- P. Pickles Pickleman?

01:01.895 --> 01:02.979
Big whoop.

01:03.062 --> 01:04.063
- Big whoop indeed!

01:04.147 --> 01:05.230
Whoop, whoop!

01:05.315 --> 01:06.983
{\an1}He's the CEO
and majority shareholder

01:07.066 --> 01:09.360
{\an1}of Picklemart Enterprises.
Duh.

01:09.444 --> 01:11.988
- Pig, it says here
they're looking for somebody

01:12.071 --> 01:13.573
to be the new
pickle mascot.

01:13.656 --> 01:16.075
- Oh, you'd be
great for that!

01:16.159 --> 01:19.329
- [gasps]
Ah.

01:19.412 --> 01:20.330
- You okay, Pig?

01:20.413 --> 01:21.581
- Quiet, everyone.

01:21.664 --> 01:22.582
I'm having a pickle
hallucination.

01:22.665 --> 01:25.043
- [grunts]

01:25.126 --> 01:28.880
I want you to be the next
mascot of the Picklemart, Pig.

01:28.963 --> 01:30.089
{\an1}- Me?

01:30.173 --> 01:30.632
{\an1}[laughs]

01:30.715 --> 01:33.384
[whooshing]

01:33.468 --> 01:34.719
[yells]

01:34.803 --> 01:35.845
[laughs]

01:35.929 --> 01:37.180
[thuds]
Ow!

01:37.263 --> 01:38.181
Got to go!

01:38.264 --> 01:40.725
I have a date with destiny.

01:40.809 --> 01:42.602
Window!

01:42.685 --> 01:43.937
{\an1}- [sips]

01:45.146 --> 01:45.688
[whooshing]

01:45.772 --> 01:48.024
- Eyeball!

01:48.107 --> 01:51.778
Mr. Manelli, I'm here to be
the new Picklemart mascot.

01:51.861 --> 01:53.488
- Too late, Pigface.

01:53.571 --> 01:55.281
{\an3}He's already doing
my butt measurements

01:55.365 --> 01:56.366
for the pickle mascot suit.

01:56.449 --> 01:57.951
{\an1}- Mm-hmm.

01:58.034 --> 02:00.161
{\an1}- But my pickle hallucination
said I could have the job,

02:00.245 --> 02:01.204
so when do I start?

02:01.287 --> 02:02.705
{\an3}- Hm.

02:02.789 --> 02:07.210
Two totally qualified employees
vying for the same job.

02:07.293 --> 02:11.047
I'll have to do what all
small business managers do.

02:11.131 --> 02:13.550
Throw a big contest!

02:13.633 --> 02:17.095
- [groans]

02:17.178 --> 02:20.431
- Make all the disappointed
lip smacks you like, McGirk,

02:20.515 --> 02:22.851
but I'm still throwing
a big contest.

02:22.934 --> 02:23.810
{\an1}- Ooh!

02:23.893 --> 02:24.811
Can I be in it?

02:24.894 --> 02:26.688
- Yes, that's the point.

02:26.771 --> 02:28.356
You're competing
with Clerk McGirk

02:28.439 --> 02:30.191
over the Pickle mascot job.

02:30.275 --> 02:32.944
{\an1}- Ooh!
Can he be in it, too?

02:33.027 --> 02:35.405
- Yes!
I just said he was--

02:35.488 --> 02:37.532
- Can she be in it?

02:37.615 --> 02:39.075
- That's a garbage can, Pig.

02:39.158 --> 02:41.411
So no, she can't.

02:41.494 --> 02:42.579
- Ugh, tough break.

02:42.662 --> 02:44.581
I tried.

02:44.664 --> 02:47.792
- You ready to rumble?
- Sure am!

02:47.876 --> 02:48.877
♪ I'm gonna win ♪

02:48.960 --> 02:50.128
♪ I'm-a gonna win ♪

02:50.211 --> 02:52.922
Unless you win.
Then I won't win.

02:53.006 --> 02:54.841
<i>- Ultimate sign spinning!</i>

02:54.924 --> 02:55.967
[explosion]

02:56.050 --> 02:58.970
<i>[rock music]</i>

02:59.053 --> 03:01.639
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:01.723 --> 03:04.267
[cheers]

03:04.350 --> 03:06.102
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:06.185 --> 03:07.103
[whooshing]

03:07.186 --> 03:08.354
- Ow, man!

03:08.438 --> 03:09.355
[crowd gasping]

03:09.439 --> 03:12.442
<i>[Island rhythmic music]</i>

03:12.525 --> 03:14.611
- Sorry!

03:14.694 --> 03:15.653
<i>[militaristic drumming]</i>

03:15.737 --> 03:17.322
- So sad.

03:17.405 --> 03:19.782
<i>Precision t-shirt cannon!</i>

03:19.866 --> 03:20.867
[explosion]

03:20.950 --> 03:23.912
<i>[rock music]</i>

03:23.995 --> 03:25.204
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:25.288 --> 03:27.290
[cheers]

03:27.373 --> 03:28.416
[explosion]

03:28.499 --> 03:30.043
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:30.126 --> 03:31.794
[cheers]

03:31.878 --> 03:33.963
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:34.047 --> 03:35.298
- [grunting]

03:35.381 --> 03:36.382
[explosion]

03:36.466 --> 03:38.968
[gagging]

03:39.052 --> 03:40.553
{\an3}- Mm-hmm.

03:40.637 --> 03:42.764
Yo, that's messed up, son.

03:43.848 --> 03:45.183
- [gags]

03:45.266 --> 03:46.184
<i>[drum roll]</i>

03:46.267 --> 03:47.143
- Pathetic.

03:47.226 --> 03:48.645
- [muffled speech]

03:48.728 --> 03:50.939
<i>- 100 pickle dash.</i>

03:51.022 --> 03:51.940
[explosion]

03:52.023 --> 03:53.858
Look alive, contenders!

03:53.942 --> 03:57.487
We have one event left,
and winner takes all!

03:57.570 --> 04:01.240
First to get to the
Pickle mascot costume wins.

04:01.324 --> 04:02.325
- Oh!

04:02.408 --> 04:04.410
So beautiful!

04:04.494 --> 04:07.830
{\an1}- Yeah.
It's as good as mine.

04:07.914 --> 04:10.333
- Runners, on your mark.

04:10.416 --> 04:11.668
Go!

04:11.751 --> 04:15.088
- [whines]

04:15.171 --> 04:16.172
[both panting]

04:16.255 --> 04:19.175
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:19.257 --> 04:20.218
I'm doing it!

04:20.301 --> 04:22.095
I'm gonna win!

04:22.178 --> 04:23.888
Nothing can stop me now!

04:23.972 --> 04:26.015
<i>[angelic music]</i>

04:26.099 --> 04:27.850
- [crying]

04:27.934 --> 04:30.019
I dropped my pickle!

04:30.103 --> 04:31.479
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:31.562 --> 04:33.856
- Oh no, poor kid.

04:33.940 --> 04:35.441
- Ha ha ha ha ha.

04:35.525 --> 04:37.443
- [crying]
- [whimpering]

04:37.527 --> 04:38.653
{\an1}Hey, what's wrong,
little girl?

04:38.736 --> 04:42.198
Everybody should be happy
at the Picklemart.

04:42.281 --> 04:43.700
Hey, look at this.

04:43.783 --> 04:45.368
<i>[wacky music]</i>

04:45.451 --> 04:47.829
- [laughing]

04:47.912 --> 04:49.914
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:49.998 --> 04:50.873
[laughing]

04:50.957 --> 04:53.251
both: Aww.

04:53.334 --> 04:54.210
- I won!

04:54.293 --> 04:57.046
I'm the new pickle mascot!

04:57.130 --> 05:01.342
♪ I am the new pickle mascot! ♪

05:01.426 --> 05:03.511
- Not so fast.

05:06.055 --> 05:07.056
- Ta da!

05:07.140 --> 05:08.224
[all gasping]

05:08.307 --> 05:09.684
- [gasps]
You're--

05:09.767 --> 05:12.145
{\an3}- P. Pickles Pickleman,
CEO and majority shareholder

05:12.228 --> 05:14.522
of Picklemart Enterprises.

05:14.605 --> 05:16.441
Congratulations, Pig.

05:16.524 --> 05:18.735
{\an3}You passed the real
final test.

05:18.818 --> 05:21.821
{\an3}You showed compassion
to our pickled children,

05:21.904 --> 05:24.824
the cornerstone of being
a true Picklemart mascot.

05:24.907 --> 05:25.783
{\an3}- Ah!

05:25.867 --> 05:26.909
- Uh, I did?

05:26.993 --> 05:29.704
- [grunting]

05:29.787 --> 05:35.918
- Pig, I hereby declare you
the new Picklemart mascot!

05:36.002 --> 05:37.295
- Yippee!

05:37.378 --> 05:38.421
[laughs]

05:38.504 --> 05:39.088
[cheering]
[camera bulb flashing]

05:39.172 --> 05:41.382
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

05:41.466 --> 05:42.759
[crunching]
[all gasping]

05:42.842 --> 05:44.469
[munching]

05:44.552 --> 05:45.970
- You ate me!

05:46.054 --> 05:48.222
{\an3}[laughs]

05:49.348 --> 05:52.685
[electronic music]

05:52.769 --> 05:54.103
- Ha ha!

05:54.187 --> 05:56.439
I finally defeated
Emperor Fudge Finger!

05:56.522 --> 05:59.650
And it's only...
5:30 a.m.?

05:59.734 --> 06:02.695
I need this day
pushed back.

06:02.779 --> 06:05.990
I'll go ask the sun.

06:06.074 --> 06:09.118
[grunting]

06:09.202 --> 06:10.328
Come on!

06:10.411 --> 06:12.038
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

06:12.121 --> 06:13.414
{\an1}Yo, Sun!

06:13.498 --> 06:16.042
- Good morning, Banana!

06:16.125 --> 06:19.504
{\an3}And what a beautiful
morning it is.

06:19.587 --> 06:20.797
- All right, look...

06:20.880 --> 06:22.298
I was up all night
playing video games.

06:22.381 --> 06:23.883
[yawns]
Just do me a solid,

06:23.966 --> 06:25.551
don't shine for a few hours

06:25.635 --> 06:26.928
so I can get some sleep.

06:27.011 --> 06:27.637
- Don't be silly.

06:27.720 --> 06:29.847
It's morning, baby!

06:29.931 --> 06:32.058
{\an1}- Come on,
just a few hours.

06:32.141 --> 06:34.894
{\an3}- Morning!

06:34.977 --> 06:36.813
{\an1}- [yawns]

06:36.896 --> 06:38.981
{\an1}Listen, Sun,
all I'm asking you,

06:39.065 --> 06:40.733
is to step out of
the sky for a bit.

06:40.817 --> 06:44.403
Take a nap or something with
all the other space garbage.

06:44.487 --> 06:45.321
{\an1}[yawns]

06:45.404 --> 06:47.990
- You think I'm garbage?

06:48.074 --> 06:50.660
[cries]

06:50.743 --> 06:52.662
- No, no, no!
I--no, what I mean--

06:52.745 --> 06:54.163
- You're right.

06:54.247 --> 06:56.415
I am space garbage.

06:56.499 --> 06:58.334
{\an3}[crying]

06:58.417 --> 07:02.338
{\an3}Well, you won't ever have
to see this space garbage again!

07:02.421 --> 07:03.339
{\an3}[cries]

07:03.422 --> 07:06.509
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

07:08.219 --> 07:12.014
- Hm.
Simple-dee-do.

07:12.098 --> 07:13.432
<i>[lullaby music]</i>

07:13.516 --> 07:15.852
[snores]

07:15.935 --> 07:17.687
{\an1}- Oh!
The sun's not up!

07:17.770 --> 07:21.858
Time to resume my
nocturnal hooting exercises.

07:21.941 --> 07:23.776
Yes.

07:23.860 --> 07:25.403
Ah hoot, hoot,
hoot, hoot.

07:25.486 --> 07:27.321
{\an5}Ah hoot, hoot,
hoot, hoot.

07:27.405 --> 07:29.198
Ah hoot, hoot,
hoot, hoot.

07:29.282 --> 07:31.033
- [groaning]

07:31.117 --> 07:32.493
- Hoot, hoot, hoot.

07:32.577 --> 07:34.078
{\an1}[screams]

07:34.162 --> 07:35.746
- Ugh!
[spitting]

07:35.830 --> 07:39.458
- How dare you throw
a boot at my fun tub!

07:39.542 --> 07:41.544
[squishing]

07:41.627 --> 07:42.712
Hmph!

07:42.795 --> 07:43.713
- [spits]

07:43.796 --> 07:44.213
- Oh!

07:44.297 --> 07:47.717
[screams]

07:47.800 --> 07:48.759
- [belches]
[snores]

07:48.843 --> 07:51.012
<i>[lullaby music]</i>

07:51.095 --> 07:52.722
[Mariachi music]

07:52.805 --> 07:54.390
What in the who hah?

07:54.473 --> 07:55.433
♪ ♪

07:55.516 --> 07:59.270
{\an1}Hey, you noisy punks,
quiet down!

07:59.353 --> 08:00.521
- Senor, it's nighttime.

08:00.605 --> 08:03.983
And nighttime equals
mariachi time.

08:04.066 --> 08:05.693
♪ ♪

08:05.776 --> 08:07.653
- Ah hoot, hoot,
hoot, hoot.

08:07.737 --> 08:09.864
Ah hoot, hoot--
- Gah!

08:10.907 --> 08:12.074
[sawing]

08:12.158 --> 08:14.035
{\an1}[grunting]

08:14.118 --> 08:15.203
{\an1}[yells]

08:15.286 --> 08:15.953
[crash]

08:16.037 --> 08:17.830
♪ ♪

08:17.914 --> 08:19.415
- Ah hoot, hoot,
hoot, hoot.

08:19.498 --> 08:22.585
- Crummy nighttime
mariachi possums!

08:22.668 --> 08:24.378
Ugh!
Finally!

08:24.462 --> 08:25.755
[snores]

08:25.838 --> 08:27.715
<i>[lullaby music]</i>

08:27.798 --> 08:29.091
<i>[creepy organ music]</i>

08:29.175 --> 08:32.428
[squeaking]

08:32.510 --> 08:33.596
{\an1}- Bleh!

08:33.679 --> 08:37.183
Nighttime equals
Banana blood-sucking time.

08:37.265 --> 08:38.601
[laughs]

08:38.683 --> 08:39.936
- [screams]

08:40.019 --> 08:43.105
{\an1}- [grunts]

08:43.188 --> 08:44.941
{\an3}- Help!
Help!

08:45.024 --> 08:46.984
[screams]

08:47.068 --> 08:48.945
- Ah hoot, hoot, hoot.

08:49.028 --> 08:51.405
{\an3}- [screams]

08:51.489 --> 08:54.200
All I wanted to was a little
sleep away from daylight,

08:54.283 --> 08:56.619
but these nocturnal nitwits
are even worse.

08:56.702 --> 08:57.912
Oh!

08:57.995 --> 08:59.080
[possums singing mariachi music]

08:59.163 --> 09:00.665
Aah!
I got to get the sun back!

09:00.748 --> 09:01.707
{\an1}- [roars]

09:01.791 --> 09:03.042
- [groans]

09:03.125 --> 09:05.294
[screams]

09:05.378 --> 09:06.754
Listen, Sun,

09:06.837 --> 09:07.964
you need to go
back in the sky again.

09:08.047 --> 09:09.924
Please?

09:10.007 --> 09:12.093
- I'm not going
back in the sky.

09:12.176 --> 09:14.845
{\an1}You said some very hurtful
things to me.

09:14.929 --> 09:17.056
You called me
"space garbage."

09:17.139 --> 09:18.516
[cries]

09:18.599 --> 09:19.976
- I know, I know.

09:20.059 --> 09:21.727
{\an3}I'm sorry for calling
you space garbage.

09:21.811 --> 09:25.481
{\an3}Can you--can you please
go back in the sky

09:25.564 --> 09:26.649
and shine again?

09:26.732 --> 09:28.818
- But I'm ugly!

09:28.901 --> 09:30.236
[sobs]

09:30.319 --> 09:32.238
- No, no, no, you're not!

09:32.321 --> 09:34.282
You have a beautiful,

09:34.365 --> 09:38.452
really wide, hot face.

09:38.536 --> 09:39.453
- Really?

09:39.537 --> 09:40.496
- Totally!

09:40.579 --> 09:41.956
- Say I'm pretty.

09:42.039 --> 09:43.666
Say I'm a pretty sun.

09:43.749 --> 09:44.709
{\an3}- [sighs]

09:44.792 --> 09:46.127
You're a pretty sun.

09:46.210 --> 09:48.379
You're so pretty,
I could kiss you.

09:48.462 --> 09:49.630
- All right.

09:49.714 --> 09:51.090
Then kiss me.

09:51.173 --> 09:52.049
- What?

09:52.133 --> 09:53.426
- Come on.

09:53.509 --> 09:54.468
[smooching]

09:54.552 --> 09:55.511
- Ugh.

09:55.594 --> 09:56.971
[lips smacking]

09:57.054 --> 09:59.181
<i>[romantic music]</i>

09:59.265 --> 10:01.350
[fire roars]

10:01.434 --> 10:03.394
{\an3}[yells]

10:03.477 --> 10:04.937
[whooshing]

10:05.021 --> 10:07.023
- Whee!

10:07.106 --> 10:09.525
- I'm so exhausted,

10:09.608 --> 10:12.361
I could fall asleep
right here.

10:12.445 --> 10:13.487
[snores]

10:13.571 --> 10:16.282
{\an3}- Banana!
There you are!

10:16.365 --> 10:17.908
You're late for work!

10:17.992 --> 10:19.660
{\an3}You got a lot of work
ahead of you today.

10:19.744 --> 10:22.538
{\an3}Chopping wood,
cleaning your cabin,

10:22.621 --> 10:24.915
{\an3}digging a ditch,
filling in that ditch,

10:24.999 --> 10:26.667
{\an3}greasing the ducks,
digging another ditch.

10:28.961 --> 10:31.130
- Oh boy, Burgerstein,

10:31.213 --> 10:33.716
today is
Genius Appreciation Day.

10:33.799 --> 10:36.177
{\an1}That means I, the resident
genius, get presents!

10:36.260 --> 10:39.847
- [speaking gibberish]

10:39.930 --> 10:40.765
- What?

10:40.848 --> 10:41.974
- [speaking gibberish]

10:42.058 --> 10:43.434
- Presents.
- [speaks gibberish]

10:43.517 --> 10:45.144
- Presents!
- [speaks gibberish]

10:45.227 --> 10:48.230
- And I refuse to accept another
year of crummy gifts

10:48.314 --> 10:50.066
from Pig, Goat, and Banana.

10:50.149 --> 10:51.567
Nothing like last year.

10:51.650 --> 10:53.611
Lint!
They all gave me lint.

10:53.694 --> 10:54.612
[grunts]

10:54.695 --> 10:56.113
No!

10:56.197 --> 11:00.368
This year, I want them to get me
a new super-deluxe lab coat.

11:00.451 --> 11:05.039
Oh, it even has that extra
pocket I can't live without.

11:05.122 --> 11:06.582
[laughs]

11:06.665 --> 11:10.002
And I can get them to do it
by planting the idea

11:10.086 --> 11:11.587
in their dreams!

11:11.670 --> 11:14.465
With my Dream Machine 9000!

11:14.548 --> 11:15.966
[laughs]

11:16.050 --> 11:18.427
I knew I'd find an excuse
to use this thing on them.

11:18.511 --> 11:20.513
<i>[ominous music]</i>

11:20.596 --> 11:21.972
- [snores]

11:22.056 --> 11:25.059
{\an1}- Let's dive into
snooze-land, shall we?

11:25.142 --> 11:26.769
{\an1}I'll start with you,
Banana.

11:26.852 --> 11:28.104
[thudding]

11:28.187 --> 11:32.358
{\an1}- Hold on, Cricket's a comin'
to your dreams!

11:32.441 --> 11:34.110
[metallic clanking]

11:34.193 --> 11:35.111
[beep]

11:35.194 --> 11:36.612
[air expelling]

11:36.695 --> 11:38.114
[explosion]

11:38.197 --> 11:39.615
Wow!

11:39.698 --> 11:43.327
A dream inhabited by
amorphous yellow globules.

11:43.411 --> 11:44.453
But where's Banana?

11:44.537 --> 11:45.788
- I'm over here!

11:45.871 --> 11:47.289
[bubbling]

11:47.373 --> 11:49.041
{\an3}And here.

11:49.125 --> 11:50.459
{\an1}And here.

11:50.543 --> 11:52.628
- Come back!
I have to tell you something.

11:52.711 --> 11:56.424
- Can't, I'm too busy being an
amorphous yellow banana globule.

11:56.507 --> 11:58.259
- But it's important!

11:58.342 --> 11:59.301
[bubbling]

11:59.385 --> 12:01.303
- Uh, all right.

12:01.387 --> 12:02.263
{\an1}- Okay.

12:02.346 --> 12:04.640
{\an1}For my present,
I want you to get me--

12:04.723 --> 12:06.684
- Oh, what--what?
I can't hear you.

12:06.767 --> 12:07.143
[creaking]

12:07.226 --> 12:09.019
- [grunting]

12:09.103 --> 12:11.439
{\an3}I said...

12:11.522 --> 12:12.565
{\an1}Lab coat!

12:12.648 --> 12:14.400
{\an3}- Uh, what?

12:14.483 --> 12:15.568
- I want a lab coat!

12:15.651 --> 12:16.819
Can you hear me?

12:16.902 --> 12:19.613
{\an3}[screams]

12:19.697 --> 12:20.823
- [belches]

12:20.906 --> 12:22.575
- [screams]

12:22.658 --> 12:24.243
{\an1}Aah!

12:24.326 --> 12:25.369
Cricket: zero.

12:25.453 --> 12:27.246
Humiliating failure: one.

12:27.329 --> 12:30.040
Even in his sleep,
he's aggravating!

12:30.124 --> 12:32.918
- ♪ I am blinded
by my own beauty ♪

12:33.002 --> 12:35.087
♪ Which makes it really
hard to apply-- ♪

12:35.171 --> 12:36.338
[snores]

12:36.422 --> 12:37.465
[air expelling]

12:37.548 --> 12:38.632
[explosion]

12:38.716 --> 12:41.510
{\an3}[singing]

12:41.594 --> 12:43.471
- Oh, Goat.
Sweet Goat.

12:43.554 --> 12:47.391
Your mind is a beautiful,
harmless forest.

12:47.475 --> 12:49.685
I'll butter her up
with a flower first.

12:49.768 --> 12:52.313
Then I'll tell her to buy me
the lab coat.

12:52.396 --> 12:55.024
Simple-dee-dang.

12:55.107 --> 12:56.108
{\an3}- [screams]

12:56.192 --> 12:57.234
{\an3}Oh, man!

12:57.318 --> 12:59.278
Oh, you monster!

12:59.361 --> 13:01.989
{\an3}[sobs]
Just end it, man!

13:02.072 --> 13:03.657
{\an3}End it!

13:03.741 --> 13:06.368
{\an3}- Oh, did you
hurt my flower?

13:06.452 --> 13:08.245
- [sobs]
Oh, yeah, he did!

13:08.329 --> 13:09.705
Oh, this guy's crazy, man.

13:09.788 --> 13:10.748
[cries]

13:10.831 --> 13:13.334
No!
I'm going into shock!

13:13.417 --> 13:14.376
I'm going into shock.

13:14.460 --> 13:15.711
[crunching]

13:15.794 --> 13:19.048
- Then you must pay the price
for hurting the flowers.

13:19.131 --> 13:21.967
- All right,
can you break a 20?

13:22.051 --> 13:24.011
<i>[harp music]</i>

13:24.094 --> 13:27.014
- [screaming]

13:27.097 --> 13:28.557
{\an1}- [yells]

13:28.641 --> 13:30.351
<i>[rock music]</i>

13:30.434 --> 13:34.230
Oh! You're just gonna
lay me on the soft, pretty...

13:34.313 --> 13:34.730
- [roars]

13:34.813 --> 13:36.857
- Scary flowers?

13:36.941 --> 13:38.275
No, don't drop me!

13:38.359 --> 13:39.568
I want to live!

13:39.652 --> 13:40.736
[yells]

13:40.819 --> 13:41.820
- [gulps]

13:41.904 --> 13:44.615
- [yells]

13:44.698 --> 13:46.617
[screams]
- [snoring]

13:46.700 --> 13:47.993
- Unbelievable!

13:48.077 --> 13:50.162
Another bust.

13:50.246 --> 13:52.414
Oh, Pig.
Sweet, simple Pig.

13:52.498 --> 13:56.252
Nothing bad could possibly
reside in your empty mind.

13:56.335 --> 13:58.045
- ♪ Scrubbing my ham flaps ♪

13:58.128 --> 13:59.463
♪ Scrubbing my ham flaps ♪

13:59.547 --> 14:02.299
♪ Flippy flippy
floppy ham flaps ♪

14:02.383 --> 14:03.509
[snores]

14:03.592 --> 14:04.843
[air expelling]

14:04.927 --> 14:06.303
[explosion]

14:07.680 --> 14:08.889
- Hi, Pig
- Hi, Cricket.

14:08.973 --> 14:12.935
{\an1}- For Genius Appreciation Day,
I want you to buy me--

14:13.018 --> 14:16.522
{\an3}- Aren't you going to
say hi to my dream donkey?

14:16.605 --> 14:17.606
[donkey brays]

14:17.690 --> 14:20.192
- Um, hi, donkey?

14:20.276 --> 14:21.277
- Now marry it.

14:21.360 --> 14:23.821
- Wait, what?

14:23.904 --> 14:28.826
- Do you take this dream donkey
to be your lawful-wedded donkey?

14:28.909 --> 14:30.160
[donkey brays]

14:30.244 --> 14:31.120
- Pig, focus!

14:31.203 --> 14:32.580
Please get me a lab coat.

14:32.663 --> 14:36.125
{\an1}It's like a big white jacket
that scientists wear.

14:36.208 --> 14:38.252
- Okay, sure.

14:38.335 --> 14:40.129
{\an1}- Really?
Yes!

14:40.212 --> 14:44.216
- I now pronounce you
Cricket and Donkey.

14:44.300 --> 14:46.302
{\an1}- Great!
I-I mean, no!

14:46.385 --> 14:47.970
- [donkey brays]
- Ew, ew, ew, ew, ew!

14:48.053 --> 14:49.138
- [slurping]

14:49.221 --> 14:50.097
{\an3}[gasps]

14:50.180 --> 14:51.890
I had the strangest dream.

14:51.974 --> 14:54.727
{\an3}But someone's getting
a special present

14:54.810 --> 14:57.313
for Genius Appreciation Day.

14:57.396 --> 14:58.397
[electricity fizzling]

14:58.480 --> 14:59.982
{\an3}[laughs]

15:00.065 --> 15:02.776
{\an1}- [gasps]
It worked!

15:02.860 --> 15:04.653
I'm getting a lab coat!

15:04.737 --> 15:06.947
- [speaking gibberish]

15:07.031 --> 15:11.285
{\an1}- This is gonna be the greatest
Genius Appreciation Day ever!

15:13.662 --> 15:15.497
{\an1}- Goat, girl,
you been bitin' your nails?

15:15.581 --> 15:17.583
- No.
- Mind if I do?

15:17.666 --> 15:19.335
[both laughing]

15:19.418 --> 15:20.544
[machine beeps]

15:20.628 --> 15:22.004
[squeaking]

15:22.087 --> 15:23.464
[machine whirring]
- [purrs]

15:23.547 --> 15:25.883
{\an1}Wanda, do you think
my horns are too big?

15:25.966 --> 15:27.509
{\an3}- Them horns are
nothing, girl.

15:27.593 --> 15:29.845
You want to talk about big,
you better go across street

15:29.928 --> 15:30.804
and see that dog.

15:30.888 --> 15:32.014
- What?
- [louder] Dog.

15:32.097 --> 15:33.349
- Excuse me?
- Dog!

15:33.432 --> 15:34.892
- How's that?
- [yelling] Dog!

15:34.975 --> 15:37.561
- Step right up
and see Moby Woof,

15:37.645 --> 15:38.896
the world's biggest dog!

15:38.979 --> 15:42.858
Look in both amazement and
disgust at this enormous,

15:42.941 --> 15:44.526
slobbering hound!

15:44.610 --> 15:46.362
- The world's biggest dog?

15:46.445 --> 15:48.238
Oh!
This I got to see.

15:48.322 --> 15:49.239
Come here.

15:49.323 --> 15:50.199
[smooches]

15:50.282 --> 15:52.368
- [chomping]
- Oh! Hey!

15:52.451 --> 15:55.412
{\an1}- Step right up
and see the world's biggest dog

15:55.496 --> 15:57.122
chewing on a goat, folks.

15:57.206 --> 15:59.541
{\an1}Right here,
in front of your face.

15:59.625 --> 16:00.501
- Ugh!

16:00.584 --> 16:02.127
Aah!
My horn!

16:02.211 --> 16:03.921
<i>[lively music]</i>

16:04.004 --> 16:04.963
- [barking]

16:05.047 --> 16:07.549
[crashing]

16:07.633 --> 16:09.468
- Hey!
Give me back my horn!

16:09.551 --> 16:11.178
- [barks]

16:11.261 --> 16:12.554
[crashing]
[car alarm blares]

16:12.638 --> 16:14.890
- Oh, I'll never catch him.

16:14.973 --> 16:16.767
What's the use?

16:16.850 --> 16:19.770
<i>[solemn music]</i>

16:19.853 --> 16:23.649
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:23.732 --> 16:26.402
{\an1}- Hey, Goat,
what's the matter?

16:26.485 --> 16:29.863
{\an3}- Oh, Moby Woof
took my horn.

16:29.947 --> 16:32.199
- I've got a great idea.

16:32.282 --> 16:33.575
- You do?

16:33.659 --> 16:34.243
[metal clanking]

16:34.326 --> 16:35.411
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

16:35.494 --> 16:38.205
- You look amazing.

16:38.288 --> 16:41.834
And now you can help me
flip my pickle pancakes!

16:43.502 --> 16:46.296
- [grumbling]
Okay.

16:46.380 --> 16:48.048
[squishing]

16:48.132 --> 16:50.551
You just taught me
a valuable lesson.

16:50.634 --> 16:52.803
- I did? What?
- I don't know.

16:52.886 --> 16:56.557
{\an3}But I'm going to find
that dog and get my horn back!

16:56.640 --> 16:57.599
- Flippy flippy!

16:57.683 --> 17:00.102
[tires screeching]

17:00.185 --> 17:01.270
[squishes]

17:01.353 --> 17:04.857
<i>[stealthy music]</i>

17:04.940 --> 17:06.066
- Hm?
[shimmering tone]

17:06.150 --> 17:07.233
- Hey!

17:07.317 --> 17:09.486
He's using my horn
for an earring!

17:09.569 --> 17:12.239
Oh, actually,
that's kind of style-y.

17:12.321 --> 17:13.949
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:14.031 --> 17:14.450
Atta doggy.

17:14.532 --> 17:16.785
Get the bone.

17:16.868 --> 17:18.579
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:18.662 --> 17:20.705
You want the bone.

17:20.789 --> 17:21.707
- [chomping]

17:21.790 --> 17:23.333
{\an1}- Ha ha!
Got ya!

17:23.416 --> 17:26.295
[clanking]

17:26.377 --> 17:28.130
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:28.213 --> 17:30.174
[grunting]

17:30.257 --> 17:32.092
[car door opening and closing]

17:32.176 --> 17:33.302
[squeaking]

17:33.385 --> 17:35.012
[shimmering tone]

17:35.095 --> 17:36.847
<i>[lively music]</i>

17:36.930 --> 17:37.890
[engine revving]

17:37.973 --> 17:38.849
Whoa!

17:38.932 --> 17:39.892
[horn honking]

17:39.975 --> 17:41.560
[crashing]

17:41.643 --> 17:44.438
[yelling]

17:44.521 --> 17:46.398
[tries screeching]

17:46.482 --> 17:47.524
[crash]

17:47.608 --> 17:49.276
Freak Giant Dog: 1.

17:49.359 --> 17:50.444
Goat: 0.

17:50.527 --> 17:52.029
[electricity buzzing]
[groans]

17:52.112 --> 17:53.739
[grunting]

17:53.822 --> 17:56.492
Okay, no dog
can resist a mailman.

17:56.575 --> 17:59.870
Especially an inflatable one
sprayed with cat juice.

17:59.953 --> 18:01.705
[cat meows]

18:01.789 --> 18:03.081
[laughs menacingly]

18:03.165 --> 18:06.043
When he goes after it,
he's gonna get a face-load

18:06.126 --> 18:07.211
of tranquilizers.

18:07.294 --> 18:09.880
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:09.963 --> 18:12.299
- [barks and growls]

18:12.382 --> 18:14.009
- Ah!
Here we go.

18:14.092 --> 18:16.053
- [barks]

18:16.136 --> 18:17.262
{\an3}- [yells]

18:17.346 --> 18:18.597
{\an3}[gags]

18:20.307 --> 18:21.183
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:21.266 --> 18:23.602
{\an3}Ah!
No, no, no, no!

18:23.685 --> 18:24.686
[air expelling]
No pain!

18:24.770 --> 18:26.230
[yells]

18:26.313 --> 18:27.523
[thuds]

18:27.606 --> 18:30.776
[deep-voiced]
I am feeling so weird, dude.

18:30.859 --> 18:33.111
Oh, look at my hands!

18:33.195 --> 18:36.198
[laughs]

18:39.368 --> 18:40.327
{\an3}- [chomps]

18:40.410 --> 18:41.370
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:41.453 --> 18:43.580
[barks]

18:43.664 --> 18:47.376
- [deep-voiced] Oh, no!
My other horn!

18:47.459 --> 18:49.378
[thuds]

18:49.461 --> 18:51.296
- [snoring]

18:51.380 --> 18:54.800
- Best friends assemble!

18:54.883 --> 18:56.218
all: Ugh.

18:56.301 --> 18:57.719
- Yeah, I know.
They're gone.

18:57.803 --> 18:59.721
And I have a plan
to get them back,

18:59.805 --> 19:01.431
but I need your help.

19:01.515 --> 19:02.808
{\an3}- Uh-oh.

19:02.891 --> 19:05.477
- Will you do it
for ol' Goaty?

19:05.561 --> 19:07.145
- All right.

19:07.229 --> 19:09.773
But only 'cause you called
yourself ol' Goaty.

19:09.857 --> 19:11.358
- Okay, great!
Here's the plan:

19:11.441 --> 19:13.944
we know he's obsessed
with horns, so...

19:14.027 --> 19:16.029
<i>[lively music]</i>

19:16.113 --> 19:17.614
- Extra!
Extra!

19:17.698 --> 19:19.867
"Bring In Da Horns,
Bring In Da Funk,"

19:19.950 --> 19:22.744
the greatest
horn-centric musical ever...

19:22.828 --> 19:23.704
- [barks]

19:23.787 --> 19:25.080
- Opens tonight!

19:25.163 --> 19:27.583
Excellent seats still
available!

19:27.666 --> 19:29.042
- [sniffs]
[chomps]

19:29.126 --> 19:30.586
- Good job, Pig!

19:30.669 --> 19:32.004
He took the bait.

19:32.087 --> 19:33.505
{\an1}- Yippee!

19:35.173 --> 19:36.258
[horn blaring]

19:36.341 --> 19:37.593
- Your attention, please.

19:37.676 --> 19:39.887
The Pig Goat Banana Cricket
Theater Company

19:39.970 --> 19:42.639
proudly presents
the time-honored classic,

19:42.723 --> 19:47.060
"Bring In Da Horns,
Bring In Da Funk."

19:49.354 --> 19:51.106
- ♪ Horns horns ♪

19:51.189 --> 19:52.274
♪ We have horns ♪

19:52.357 --> 19:55.235
- ♪ Some are used to fight ♪

19:55.319 --> 19:58.113
{\an1}- ♪ Some are fun
to take a bite oh ♪

19:58.196 --> 20:00.616
both: ♪ Some are
pointy and round ♪

20:00.699 --> 20:02.451
♪ Some are fun for ♪

20:02.534 --> 20:06.079
- ♪ Making sound ♪

20:06.163 --> 20:08.040
[horn blares]

20:08.123 --> 20:09.249
all: Remix!

20:09.333 --> 20:10.292
[hip hop music]

20:10.375 --> 20:11.668
all: Horns!

20:11.752 --> 20:13.545
[as "Ride of the Valkyries" by
Richard Wagner]

20:13.629 --> 20:15.088
- ♪ Horns, horns, horns,
horns, horns ♪

20:15.172 --> 20:16.882
{\an5}♪ Horns, horns, horns,
horns, horns♪

20:16.965 --> 20:18.675
♪ Horns, horns, horns,
horns, horns ♪

20:18.759 --> 20:20.469
{\an5}♪ Horns, horns, horns,
horns, horns ♪

20:20.552 --> 20:21.470
[hair metal music]

20:21.553 --> 20:25.307
- ♪ Horns horns horns ♪

20:25.390 --> 20:26.934
♪ Rock my horns ♪

20:27.017 --> 20:28.644
- ♪ Horns horns horns
horns horns ♪

20:28.727 --> 20:29.269
Go get him, Goat!

20:29.353 --> 20:31.355
- Surprise, doggy!

20:31.438 --> 20:33.482
[growling and grunting]

20:33.565 --> 20:35.692
<i>[heavy metal music]</i>

20:35.776 --> 20:36.693
- [yelling]

20:36.777 --> 20:38.236
- [barking]

20:38.320 --> 20:39.613
{\an1}- We'll save you!
[hollers]

20:39.696 --> 20:41.865
- To the rescue!

20:41.949 --> 20:42.950
{\an3}- Oh, boy!

20:43.033 --> 20:44.326
- [barking]

20:44.409 --> 20:48.080
[all yelling]

20:48.163 --> 20:49.748
[thudding]

20:51.625 --> 20:53.001
- [barking]

20:53.085 --> 20:54.002
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:54.086 --> 20:55.504
{\an3}- Goat, did you get
your horns back?

20:55.587 --> 20:57.923
- No.

20:58.006 --> 20:59.841
But I got his teeth!

20:59.925 --> 21:01.009
<i>[angelic music]</i>

21:01.093 --> 21:02.010
- Ew.

21:02.094 --> 21:03.512
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:03.595 --> 21:04.554
- Thanks, guys.

21:04.638 --> 21:05.681
I so appreciate it.

21:05.764 --> 21:07.224
all: Yeah!

21:07.307 --> 21:08.850
Pig, Goat, Banana, Cricket,
Goat got his teeth

21:08.934 --> 21:12.771
and is using them as horns,
high-five!

21:12.854 --> 21:14.940
{\an3}- And speaking of
appreciation,

21:15.023 --> 21:17.025
{\an3}did, uh,
someone get me a gift

21:17.109 --> 21:19.361
for Genius Appreciation Day?

21:19.444 --> 21:21.071
- Oh, yeah!

21:21.154 --> 21:22.781
{\an1}Cricket, I have
a present for you!

21:22.864 --> 21:26.368
- Is it a lab coat?

21:26.451 --> 21:28.829
- Better!
It's a crab boat.

21:28.912 --> 21:29.538
[horn blaring]

21:29.621 --> 21:31.498
- Oh thank--wait, what?

21:31.581 --> 21:32.833
[thuds]

21:34.668 --> 21:36.128
[cries, stammers]

21:36.211 --> 21:39.798
{\an3}But all I wanted
was a new lab coat!

21:39.881 --> 21:43.176
One simple, measly...

21:43.260 --> 21:44.136
[gasps]

21:44.219 --> 21:45.220
The lab coat!

21:45.303 --> 21:47.264
[stammering]
It's beautiful!

21:47.347 --> 21:48.432
But who--?

21:48.515 --> 21:51.476
- [speaking gibberish]

21:51.560 --> 21:54.896
- Burgerstein?
You remembered!

21:54.980 --> 21:57.816
- [speaking gibberish]

21:57.899 --> 21:59.943
- I love you.
<i>- [speaking gibberish]</i>

22:02.154 --> 22:05.157
{\an8}<i>[gentle acoustic guitar music]</i>

